<div class="landing-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Undergraduate Research</h1>
    <p>Welcome to the Texas A&M University CSCE Honors Research Portal</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="landing-main">
    <section id="advising-info">
      <h2>Department Information</h2>
      <p>The CSCE Honors Program at Texas A&M University offers a unique
        opportunity for ambitious students to excel both personally and
        professionally in the field of Computer Science and Computer
        Engineering. This distinguished program empowers high-achieving
        students to take the lead in research, collaborate with world-class
        faculty, and drive innovation across a wide range of technological
        domains.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="drop-in-times">
      <h2>Honors Students</h2>
      <p>As a member of the CSCE Honors Program, you will gain unparalleled
        access to cutting-edge resources, personalized faculty advisement, and
        exclusive research opportunities. This portal is designed to foster
        your intellectual curiosity and push the boundaries of what is possible
        in the rapidly evolving fields of computer science and engineering.</p>
      <p>On this page, you will find valuable resources to guide your academic
        journey:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Research Opportunities:</strong>
          Explore a variety of ongoing research projects in collaboration with
          top-tier faculty members in alignment with
          <a
            href="https://engineering.tamu.edu/academics/eh/departments/csce-track/requirements.html"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Program Requirements</a></li>
        <li><strong>Faculty Contacts:</strong>
          Easily connect with experienced professors and mentors who will
          provide personalized guidance and support.</li>
        <li><strong>Program Highlights:</strong>
          Learn about the distinctive advantages of being part of the CSCE
          Honors Program and how it can accelerate your growth.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Whether you’re looking to deepen your expertise, develop innovative
        solutions, or take on leadership roles in research, you can utilize the
        tools to explore your next step. Start your journey toward excellence
        today!</p>
      <h3>
        <%# Link to the projects index page %>
        <%= link_to "Click HERE to view all available research opportunities",
        projects_path,
        class: "btn btn-primary btn-lg mt-3" %>
      </h3>
    </section>

    <section id="advisors" class="advisor-section">
      <h2>Administrative Coordinator</h2>
      <div>
        <%# Removed advisor class, adjust styling as needed %>
        <h3>Stephanie Vilas</h3>
        <p>Computer Science & Engineering<br>
          Undergraduate Honors Administrator<br>
          Office: 3112 TAMU<br>
          Email:
          <a href="mailto:stephanie.vilas@tamu.edu">stephanie.vilas@tamu.edu</a></p>
      </div>
      <%# Add more admin contacts if needed %>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>

<footer class="landing-footer">
  <div class="container">
    <p>©
      <%= Time.now.year %>
      Texas A&M University | Department of Computer Science & Engineering</p>
  </div>
</footer>
